The '''Anello del Rinascimento''' (''Ring of the Renaissance'' or ''Renaissance Ring'') is a path that people can travel on foot or by bike; it is longer than 170&nbsp;km and it traces a symbolic route around the city of [[Florence]]. The path skirts fields and woods, castles, ancient churches, and monasteries and penetrates to the heart of [[Florence]], [[Fiesole]] and other municipalities in the [[Province of Florence]]. Its central reference point is the [[Florence Cathedral]], the masterpiece of [[Filippo Brunelleschi]].
