{{italictitle}} {{taxobox |name = ''Azorella selago'' |regnum = [[Plant]]ae |unranked_divisio = [[Angiosperms]] |unranked_classis = [[Eudicots]] |unranked_ordo = [[Asterids]] |ordo = [[Apiales]] |familia = [[Apiaceae]] |genus = ''[[Azorella]]'' |species = '''''A. selago''''' |binomial = ''Azorella selago'' |binomial_authority = [[Joseph Dalton Hooker|Hook.f.]] }}
'''''Azorella selago''''' is a species of [[cushion plant]] native to the [[Subantarctic|sub-Antarctic]] islands of the [[Southern Ocean]], including the [[Crozet Islands]], the [[Possession Islands]], the [[Heard Island and McDonald Islands]], the [[Kerguelen Islands]], and the [[Prince Edward Islands]].<ref name="Bergstrom2000">{{cite web|last=Bergstrom|first=Dana|title=Indicator 70 - The presence or absence of vascular plant species in two defined areas of Heard Island|url=http://data.aad.gov.au/aadc/soe/display_indicator.cfm?soe_id=70|publisher=Australian Antarctic Data Centre, System for Indicator Management and Reporting|accessdate=2008-06-20| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080803181257/http://data.aad.gov.au/aadc/soe/display_indicator.cfm?soe_id=70| archivedate= 3 August 2008 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref><ref name="leRoux2004">{{cite journal|last=le Roux|first=Peter C.|author2=Melodie A. McGeoch|title=The use of size as an estimator of age in the Subantarctic cushion plant, ''Azorella selago'' (Apiaceae)|journal=Arctic, Antarctic, and Alpine Research|volume=36|issue=4|pages=509–517|publisher=Institute of Arctic and Alpine Research|doi=10.1657/1523-0430(2004)36[509:TUOSAA]2.0.CO;2|year=2004|issn=1523-0430}}<!--| accessdate=2008-06-20--></ref> The closely related ''[[Azorella macquariensis]]'', which is endemic to [[Macquarie Island]], was [[Lumpers and splitters|split]] from it [[Taxonomy (biology)|taxonomically]] in 1989. ''A. selago'' is often a [[keystone species]] where it occurs and is well studied for its contribution to its native ecosystems.<ref name="Bergstrom2000" /><ref name="Phiri2007">{{cite web|last=Phiri |first=Ethel E. |author2=Steven L. Chown |author3=Melodie A. McGeoch |title=Spatial distribution of mouse damage to the keystone plant species, ''Azorella selago'', on Marion Island |url=http://academic.sun.ac.za/botzoo/agm_abstracts_2007.htm |publisher=Department of Botany & Zoology, University of Stellenbosch, South Africa |ac