'''Flanders Investment and Trade''' (FIT) was founded by the [[Flemish government]] in 2005. The FIT agency helps [[Flanders|Flemish]] companies expand their business abroad and assists foreign companies in finding Flemish suppliers of quality goods and services. The FIT agency is headed by [[Christ’l Joris]].

FIT has its headquarters in Brussels (Belgium) and has 80 offices around the world. These offices provide information and support to both investors and exporters.

