{{Infobox airport | name = Kihnu Airfield | nativename = | nativename-a = | image = | IATA = | ICAO = EEKU | type = Public | owner = AS Pärnu Lennujaam | operator = | city-served = [[Pärnu]], [[Kihnu]], [[Estonia]] | location = [[Sääre, Pärnu County]] | elevation-f = 11 | coordinates = {{coord|58|08|54|N|024|00|09|E|region:EE|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = Estonia | pushpin_map_caption = Location in Estonia | pushpin_label = EEKU | website = [http://www.parnu-airport.ee/eng/associates/aviation/kihnu parnu-airport.ee/.../kihnu] | metric-rwy = y | r1-number = 04/22 | r1-length-m = 600 | r1-surface = Grass | r2-number = 15/33 | r2-length-m = 567 | r2-surface = Grass | footnotes = Sources: Estonian [[Aeronautical Information Publication|AIP]]<ref name="AIP">{{cite web|url=http://eaip.eans.ee/2016-07-21/html/index-en-GB.html |title=eAIP Estonia|publisher=[[Estonian Air Navigation Services]] (ANS) |access-date=2016-07-27}}</ref> }}
'''Kihnu Airfield''' {{airport codes||EEKU}} is an [[airfield]] on [[Kihnu|Kihnu island]] in [[Estonia]]. The airfield is situated near the village of [[Sääre, Pärnu County|Sääre]] and is {{Convert|22|NM|lk=in}} southwest of [[Pärnu]].<ref name="AIP"/> It has no [[IATA airport code]].
The airfield has two crossing [[runway]]s; 04/22 {{convert|600|x|20|m|abbr=on}} and 15/33 {{convert|567|x|60|m|abbr=on}}, both with grass surface.<ref name="AIP"/> There are no landing lights or navigational systems on the airfield. Therefore, the airfield is only certified for [[Visual flight rules|VFR]] in daylight.<ref name="AIP"/> There are no regular flights to Kihnu since [[Air Livonia]] stopped operating. Small private planes use the airfield for general flights in the summer. Also LFH does charter flights to Kihnu.
Kihnu Airfield is owned by AS Pärnu Lennujaam ([[Pärnu Airport]] Ltd).
The operators of the airfield warn that the airfield is not fenced in, so pilots who wish to land outside of the airfield's operational hours need to make sure that there are no people, animals or other obstacles on the runways before landing.<ref>[http://www.eepu.ee/index.php?sitesig=PILEN&page=PILEN_013_Kihnu_Airfield&subpage=PILEN_002_Runway eepu.ee]</ref>
