'''Letsholathebe Memorial Hospital''' is a [[government hospital|government-run]] [[Hospital#District|district hospital]] located in [[Maun, Botswana|Maun]], is the fifth largest town in [[Botswana]]. As of 2011, it had a population of 55,784. Maun is the "tourism capital" of [[Botswana]] and the administrative centre of [[North-West District (Botswana)|Ngamiland]] district.
== History == Letsholathebe Memorial hospital is established in September 2008 by the government of Botswana. The institution serves the public community in Botswana. It operates under leadership of chief medical officer Mr. [[Richard Kambinda]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gov.bw/en/Ministries--Authorities/Ministries/MinistryofHealth-MOH/Departments-of-MOH/MOA-Departments2/|title=CMO Letsholathebe Hospital|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=14 October 2017}}</ref>
