The '''Diocese of Gradisca''' (Latin: ''Dioecesis Gradisca'') was a Roman Catholic diocese located in the town of [[Gradisca d'Isonzo]] in the [[Province of Gorizia]] in [[Friuli-Venezia Giulia]]. In 1791, it was united with the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Gorizia|Archdiocese of Gorizia]] to form the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Gorizia e Gradisca|Archdiocese of Gorizia e Gradisca]].<ref name=CathHierGradisca>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dg513.html "Diocese of Gradisca (d’Isonzo)"] ''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''. David M. Cheney. Retrieved August 25, 2016{{Self-published source|date=January 2017}}</ref><ref name=GCathGradisca>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/former/t0895.htm "Titular Archiepiscopal See of Gradisca"] ''GCatholic.org''. Gabriel Chow. Retrieved August 25, 2016</ref> In 1986, it was restored as the Restored as [[titular see|Titular Archiepiscopal See]] of Gradisca.<ref name=GCathGradisca />

