{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Klerksdorp |latin = Dioecesis Klerkpolitanus |country = {{flag|South Africa}} |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Johannesburg|Johannesburg]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = Cathedral of Christ the Redeemer |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 34,800 |population = 1,500,000 |population_as_of = 2004 |catholics = 103,466 |catholics_percent= 6.9 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = Vacant see ([[sede vacante]]); Bishop [[Zithulele Patrick Mvemve]] resigned, Johannesburg's [[Archbishop]], [[Buti Joseph Tlhagale]], [[Missionary Oblates of Mary Immaculate|O.M.I.]], is [[Apostolic Administrator]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Klerksdorp''' ({{lang-la|Klerkpolitan(us)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Klerksdorp]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Johannesburg|Johannesburg]] in [[South Africa]].
The second Bishop of Klerksdorp was [[His Lordship]], the [[Right Reverend]] Bishop [[Patrick Zithulele Mvemve]], former [[Auxiliary Bishop]] of [[Johannesburg]] (while serving there, he was the [[Titular Bishop]] of [[Luperciana]]). On Friday, April 26, 2013, [[Pope Francis]] accepted Bishop Mvemve's resignation as Bishop, under Canon 401.2 of the Latin-rite [[Code of Canon Law]]. Pope Francis then appointed Johannesburg's [[Archbishop]], [[Buti Joseph Tlhagale]], [[Missionary Oblates of Mary Immaculate|O.M.I.]], as [[Apostolic Administrator]] until the third Bishop is named in the future.<ref>http://attualita.vatican.va/sala-stampa/bollettino/2013/04/26/news/30881.html</ref>
==History== * October 14, 1965: Established as Apostolic Prefecture of Western Transvaal from the Diocese of Johannesburg * February 27, 1978: Promoted as Diocese of Klerksdorp
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of Klerksdorp (Roman rite) ** Bishop [[Patrick Zithulele Mvemve]] (1994.03.26 - 2013.04.26) ** Bishop [[Daniel Alphonse Omer Verstraete]], [[O.M.I.]] (1978.02.27 – 1994.03.26) * Prefects Apostolic of Western Transvaal (Roman rite) ** Bishop Daniel Alphonse Omer Verstraete, O.M.I. (1965.11.09 – 1978.02.27) The third bishop is Victor Hlolo Phalana.
